project.name: Depot Domain IPC3
project.description:
This model was based on the strips version of the Depot domain described in the IPC-3 (2002).
This domain was devised in order to see what would happen if two previously well-researched domains were joined together. These were the logistics and blocks domains. They are combined to form a domain in which trucks can transport crates around and then the crates must be stacked onto pallets at their destinations. The stacking is achieved using hoists, so the stacking problem is like a blocks world problem with hands. Trucks can behave like "tables", since the pallets on which crates are stacked are limited.

actor.name: Truck
actor.description: This actor is responsible for transporting the crates from one place to another.

actor.name: Hoist
actor.description: This actor is responsible for arranging the crates at a place and loading then in to a truck.

useCase.name: Drive from a place to another
useCase.description: The agent truck moves from an origin place to a destination place.

definition.precondition: - the truck must at the origin place.
definition.postcondition: - the truck is at the destination place; - the fuel cost is increased.
definition.invariants: - the truck load remains the same.

useCase.name: Lift a crate
useCase.description: The agent hoist lifts a crate from a surface (a pallet or another crate) at a place.

definition.invariants: - the hoist, the crate and the surface remain at the same place.

useCase.name: Drop a crate
useCase.description: The agent hoist drops a crate on a surface (a pallet or another crate) at a place.

definition.postcondition: - the crate is on the surface; - the hoist is available.
definition.invariants: - the hoist, the crate and the surface remain at the same place.

useCase.name: Hoist load a crate in a truck
useCase.description: The agent hoist loads a crate in a truck at a place.

definition.invariants: - the truck, the crate and the hoist remain at the same place.

useCase.name: Hoist unload a crate from a truck
useCase.description: The agent hoist unload a crate from a truck at a place.

definition.invariants: - the truck, the crate and the hoist remain at the same place.

state.name: Crate being lifted
state.condition: y.clear = false and y.isIn = null and y.at = p and y.on = null

state.name: Crate on surface
state.condition: y.clear = true and y.isIn = null and y.at = p and y.on = z

state.name: Crate in truck
state.condition: y.isIn = z and y.at = null and y.on = null

state.name: Hoist lifting
state.condition: x.available = false and x.lifting = y and x.at = p

state.name: Hoist available
state.condition: x.available = true and x.lifting = null and x.at = p
